  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN156.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">talaimakaḷai yiṭattuyttu vantu talaimakaṉai varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How the confidante urged HIM for marriage after having come [back] from sending HER to the [meeting] place.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN156.2">
            <lg type="edition">
              <l>muracuṭaic celvar puravic cūṭṭu</l>
              <l>mūṭṭuṟu kavari tūkki yaṉṉa</l>
              <l>ceḻuñcey nelliṉ cēyarip puṉiṟṟuk</l>
              <l>katirmūtā tiṉṟa lañcik kāvalar</l>
              <l>pāka lāykoṭip pakaṉṟaiyoṭu parīik</l>
              <l>kāñci yiṉattuk karumparu kiyārkkun</l>
              <l>tīmpuṉa lūra tiṟava tākak</l>
              <l>kuvaḷai yuṇka ṇivaḷum yāṉuṅ</l>
              <l>kaḻunīr yāmpaṉ muḻuneṟip pakaittaḻai</l>
              <l>kāmar ñāyiṟ ṟākat talaippap</l>
              <l>poyttal pāṭip polinteṉa vantu</l>
              <l>niṉṉakāp piḻaitta tavaṟō peruma</l>
              <l>kaḷḷuṅ kaṇṇiyuṅ kaiyuṟai yāka</l>
              <l>nilaikkōṭṭu veḷḷai nālcevik kaṭāa</l>
              <l>yulaittuṟaik kaṭavuṭ kuḷappaṭa vō<supplied>cci</supplied>t</l>
              <l>taṇimarun taḻiyāḷ yāyu</l>
              <l>maṇimaruṇ mēṉi poṉṉiṟaṅ koḷalē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Oh man from a village of sweet floods, (7ab)</l>
                <l>where sugarcane in groups rattles fearfully by the Portia trees, (6)</l>
                <l>as the watchmen, afraid that the old cow might eat the ears (4)</l> 
                <l>newly born in red bunches of paddy on the rich field, (3)</l>
                <l>as if it was hung with the chowries stitched on (2)</l>
                <l>as a decoration of the horse of drum-possessing rich people, (1)</l>
                <l>tear off choice creepers of Pākal together with jalap, (5)</l>
                <l>was it for the mistake, o great one, that we went wrong in smiling at you, (12)</l>
                <l>she with waterlily-like eyes and me, so that it would be proper (7cd-8)</l>
                <l>coming because it flourished, singing lies, (11)</l>
                <l>when [you] offered, so that in the sun it would be charming, (10)</l>
                <l>foliage in contrast with whole calyxes of white lotus [and] blue waterlily, (9)</l>
                <l>that mother too, who does not despair of the appeasing remedy,</l>
                <l>put it inwardly down to the god from the ruined ghat, (16f.)</l>
                <l>urging [upon him] the hanging ears of a goat with stately(?) horns, (14)</l>
                <l>with toddy and a chaplet to be a present, (15)</l>
                <l>takes in the gold colour of [our] sapphire-like body? (17)</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="alternate" sameAs="I.9f">
              <l>He speaks indeed, friend, so that [my] heart is consumed, in order to go alone…</l>
             </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
